ciscoCableIronBusStatMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ubr@cisco.com
ciscoCableIronBusStatMIB.description: This is the MIB module for Cable Iron Bus Statistics for DOCSIS-compliant Cable Modem Termination Systems (CMTS). The Statistics of Iron Bus is a software/hardware feature provided in the CMTS so that the CMTS can count statistics of bandwidth usage of Iron Bus when traffic through it. The purpose of cable Iron Bus statistics is to monitor the bandwidth usage of Iron Bus , which CMTS can report warning message when the traffic throughput on Iron Bus overlap the threshold configured. The statistics of Iron Bus also monitor the traffic throughput statistics both ingress and outband Iron Bus with units bytes and packets per second. The statistics of Iron Bus can also configure the threshold and message interval to CMTS.

ciscoCableIronBusStatTable.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatTable
ciscoCableIronBusStatTable.description: This table abstracts a sparse matrix of Bandwidth resource utilization thresholds to be monitored by Iron Bus Statistics. The ciscoCableIronBusStatIndex uniquely identifies the physical entity with a set of Iron Bus bandwidth resource utilization thresholds being associated.The physical entities is for Jacket Card slot Number.The agent creates/destroys/modifies an entry whenever the local console affects this configuration.The management application may create/destroy/modify an entry. This entry will exist by default since the Iron Bus Statistics has 90% and 2 minutes configuration by default.

ciscoCableIronBusStatEntry.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatEntry
ciscoCableIronBusStatEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cableIronBusStatTable.

ciscoCableIronBusStatIndex.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatIndex
ciscoCableIronBusStatIndex.description: This object defines the index of this entry , which should be the slot number of SIP card in CMTS, only support 1,3 currently.

ciscoCableIronBusStatFibBandwidth.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatFibBandwidth
ciscoCableIronBusStatFibBandwidth.description: This object specifies Iron Bus Fib bandwidth(From Iron Bus) thresholds currently in CMTS being monitored.

ciscoCableIronBusStatTibBandwidth.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatTibBandwidth
ciscoCableIronBusStatTibBandwidth.description: This object specifies Iron Bus Tib bandwidth(To Iron Bus) thresholds currently in CMTS being monitored.

ciscoCableIronBusStatMessageIntervalCurr.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatMessageIntervalCurrent
ciscoCableIronBusStatMessageIntervalCurr.description: This object specifies Iron Bus warning message interval currently in CMTS being monitored. which from 0 to 60 minutes. Setting the object to 2 will remove the configuration. Setting the object to 0 will not log any warning message.

ciscoCableIronBusStatBandwidthCurrent.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatBandwidthCurrent
ciscoCableIronBusStatBandwidthCurrent.description: This object specifies Iron Bus bandwidth usage thresholds currently in CMTS being monitored. The following values range from 50 to 100. Setting the object to 90 is remove the configuration and set it to default configuration.

ciscoCableIronBusStatMessageIntervalDefa.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatMessageIntervalDefault
ciscoCableIronBusStatMessageIntervalDefa.description: This object specifies Iron Bus warning message interval by default. The default value of this object is 2.

ciscoCableIronBusStatBandwidthDefault.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatBandwidthDefault
ciscoCableIronBusStatBandwidthDefault.description: This object specifies the default Iron Bus bandwidth usage thresholds in CMTS being monitored. The default value is 90.

ciscoCableIronBusStatFibPktsRcv.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatFibPktsRcv
ciscoCableIronBusStatFibPktsRcv.description: This object specifies the Fib received packets per second.

ciscoCableIronBusStatFibBytesRcv.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatFibBytesRcv
ciscoCableIronBusStatFibBytesRcv.description: This object specifies the Fib received bytes per second.

ciscoCableIronBusStatTibPktsSent.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatTibPktsSent
ciscoCableIronBusStatTibPktsSent.description: This object specifies the Fib sent packets per second.

ciscoCableIronBusStatTibByteSent.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatTibByteSent
ciscoCableIronBusStatTibByteSent.description: This object specifies the Fib sent Bytes per second.

ciscoCableIronBusStatFibPktsPerSec.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatFibPktsPerSec
ciscoCableIronBusStatFibPktsPerSec.description: This object specifies the Fib throughput Bytes per second.

ciscoCableIronBusStatTibPktPerSec.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatTibPktPerSec
ciscoCableIronBusStatTibPktPerSec.description: This object specifies the Tib throughput Bytes per second.

ciscoCableIronBusStatMIBCompliance.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatMIBCompliance
ciscoCableIronBusStatMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco Cable Iron Bus Statistics MIB

ciscoCableIronBusStatObjectGroup.name: ciscoCableIronBusStatObjectGroup
ciscoCableIronBusStatObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects providing CMTS Iron Bus Statistics being monitored.
